Package: trizavalr
Title: Statistically Rigorous Evaluation Tooling for AI Systems
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Jason Kagaba", "Contributors", , "atuhurrasolomon47@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: R bindings to the Trizaval statistical engine, a Rust core
    providing block bootstrap confidence intervals and effect size
    estimation (Cohen's d and Hedges' g) for comparing evaluation
    results from non-deterministic AI systems. These bindings expose
    the same underlying Rust implementation used by Trizaval's Python
    package and command line tool, so results are identical across
    languages.
License: Apache License (>= 2)
Encoding: UTF-8
